{"type":"message","id":"bc424168","parentId":"332fcf8b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:19:28.060Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wk7byhc5q79q_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4332\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='tic_experiment.ps1' new_len=2797\r\n[mutation proposed] tic_experiment.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 021857 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need a concrete implementation to analyze pulse logs and test if invariant detection enables next-pulse prediction.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"grand-crest","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4332\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='tic_experiment.ps1' new_len=2797\r\n[mutation proposed] tic_experiment.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 021857 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need a concrete implementation to analyze pulse logs and test if invariant detection enables next-pulse prediction.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774333168058}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2c53c88","parentId":"bc424168","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:19:28.064Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wk7byhc5q79q_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 021757\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n3. Key pending item: TIC Experiment - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action is to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier. This is the core experiment that unifies Phase 1 and Phase 2.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist:\r\n- I need to examine the pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n- Start by analyzing the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n\r\nActually, I should first check what pulse logs exist and their structure before implementing the classifier. Let me create a script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features (invariant vs variant patterns)\r\n3. Classifies them\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC classifier implementation file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant patterns from variant patterns across pulse logs, then test next-pulse prediction. This unifies Phase 1 and Phase 2.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script implementing the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier that:\r\n1. Loads pulse logs from `logs/` directory\r\n2. Extracts temporal features (word frequency, topic patterns, structure)\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant (recurring) or variant (new)\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n5. Outputs classification report with metrics against success criteria (>70% accuracy, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests whether causal structure = invariant structure.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nOUTPUT_FILE = Path(\"research/tic_results.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse logs, sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        with open(f) as fh:\r\n            logs.append({\r\n                \"path\": f,\r\n                \"name\": f.name,\r\n                \"content\": fh.read()\r\n            })\r\n    return logs\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features for invariance detection.\"\"\"\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z]{4,}\\b', text.lower())\r\n    word_freq = Counter(words)\r\n    \r\n    # Top features\r\n    top_words = set([w for w, _ in word_freq.most_common(50)])\r\n    \r\n    # Structural features (headers, lists, code blocks)\r\n    headers = len(re.findall(r'^#{1,3}\\s', text, re.MULTILINE))\r\n    list_items = len(re.findall(r'^\\s*[-*]\\s', text, re.MULTILINE))\r\n    code_blocks = len(re.findall(r'```', text)) // 2\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"top_words\": top_words,\r\n        \"word_freq\": word_freq,\r\n        \"headers\": headers,\r\n        \"list_items\": list_items,\r\n        \"code_blocks\": code_blocks,\r\n        \"total_words\": len(words)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariance(prev_features, curr_features):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute invariance score between two pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    # Word overlap (invariant content)\r\n    overlap = prev_features[\"top_words\"] & curr_features[\"top_words\"]\r\n    word_invariance = len(overlap) / max(len(prev_features[\"top_words\"]), 1)\r\n    \r\n    # Structural similarity\r\n    struct_diff = abs(prev_features[\"headers\"] - curr_features[\"headers\"]) + \\\r\n                  abs(prev_features[\"list_items\"] - curr_features[\"list_items\"])\r\n    struct_invariance = max(0, 1 - struct_diff / 5)\r\n    \r\n    # Combined score\r\n    return 0.7 * word_invariance + 0.3 * struct_invariance\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(curr_features, future_logs, threshold=0.5):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse features and compare to actual.\"\"\"\r\n    predictions = []\r\n    for future in future_logs[:3]:  # Predict next 3 pulses\r\n        fut_feat = extract_features(future[\"content\"])\r\n        inv_score = compute_invariance(curr_features, fut_feat)\r\n        predictions.append({\r\n            \"pulse\": future[\"name\"],\r\n            \"invariance_score\": inv_score,\r\n            \"is_invariant\": inv_score >= threshold\r\n        })\r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs()\r\n    print(f\"Loaded {len(logs)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    if len(logs) < 5:\r\n        print(\"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs for TIC experiment\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Extract features for all logs\r\n    all_features = [extract_features(log[\"content\"]) for log in logs]\r\n    \r\n    # Classify each pulse (invariant vs variant relative to previous)\r\n    classifications = []\r\n    for i in range(1, len(all_features)):\r\n        score = compute_invariance(all_features[i-1], all_features[i])\r\n        is_invariant = score >= 0.5\r\n        classifications.append({\r\n            \"pulse\": logs[i][\"name\"],\r\n            \"score\": score,\r\n            \"classification\": \"INVARIANT\" if is_invariant else \"VARIANT\"\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate accuracy (manual labeling for validation subset)\r\n    # For now, assume correct classification if score > 0.5\r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:18:26\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774333168060}}
